Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.32,0:00:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to talk to you\Non the theme “Do the Math.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.56,0:00:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you heard right: “Do the Math.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, math may not be your favorite subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but as we’re going to see,\Nsomeone has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.53,0:00:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes doing the math\Nis the only way we can make a time line
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.74,0:00:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or get interesting background information
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.97,0:00:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes our Bible reading more enjoyable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.84,0:00:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you do want to make\Nyour Bible reading more enjoyable, don’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.65,0:00:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s start with a number
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.88,0:00:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we might quickly skip over\Nin our Bible reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.39,0:00:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to Matthew 19:28,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.99,0:00:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s see how a number
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.69,0:00:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,can sometimes tell us\Nmore than what’s written on the page.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 19:28:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.80,0:00:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jesus said to them: ‘Truly I say to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.21,0:00:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘in the re-creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.44,0:01:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘when the Son of man\Nsits down on his glorious throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.81,0:01:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘you who have followed me\Nwill sit on 12 thrones,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.58,0:01:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,judging the 12 tribes of Israel.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.42,0:01:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see anything interesting there?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.86,0:01:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give you a hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.19,0:01:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,These words were spoken near the end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.00,0:01:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus’ earthly ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that give you a hint?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.44,0:01:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give you another hint: the number 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.51,0:01:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, Jesus knew
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.24,0:01:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that only 11 of his apostles\Nwere going to be faithful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.81,0:01:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, he said there would be\N12 thrones in the Kingdom, not 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.38,0:01:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What did it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.39,0:01:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It meant that Judas\Nwould have to be replaced as an apostle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And sure enough, he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.89,0:01:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was easy, wasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no math involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.53,0:01:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.17,0:02:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But, let’s see how doing the math\Ncan help us to answer a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.41,0:02:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,During family worship, one of the kids asks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.54,0:02:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whether Noah and Abraham knew each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.91,0:02:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going to handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.61,0:02:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You might just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.62,0:02:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Bible doesn’t say” and leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.02,0:02:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But you could figure it out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you did the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s what we know:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.60,0:02:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Flood occurred in 2370 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.30,0:02:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that date is absolutely solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.84,0:02:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you’d like\Nto figure it out for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.24,0:02:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you can look it up under “Chronology”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.57,0:02:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Insight{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}book—2370 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.48,0:02:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the Flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.95,0:02:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And Noah lived for 350 years after the Flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So by subtracting 350 from 2370,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.56,0:02:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn that Noah died in 2020 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.46,0:02:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is,\NDid Noah and Abram know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.57,0:03:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Abram entered the land of Canaan
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.67,0:03:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1943 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.98,0:03:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, once again,\Nif you want to prove that to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.58,0:03:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,look in Insight{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}under “Chronology.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.71,0:03:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find everything\Nyou need to prove it to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So in 1943 B.C.E., Abraham
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,(Abram in that case)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.09,0:03:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,enters the land of Canaan
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s 75 years old at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.26,0:03:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So Abram must have been born
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,75 years before 1943 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.10,0:03:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Add 75 to 1943,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and you find that Abram was born
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.64,0:03:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2018 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.71,0:03:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So Noah died in 2020 B.C.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and Abram was born\Ntwo years later, in 2018 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.02,0:03:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They never knew each other, but it was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our publications have often said
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jonathan was\Nat least 30 years older than David.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Bible doesn’t say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.16,0:04:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Your progressive Bible student
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.30,0:04:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(you know, the one\Nwho makes you prove everything)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,asks you about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.80,0:04:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you prove it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can if you do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.58,0:04:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,King Saul ruled Israel for 40 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.62,0:04:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then David became king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.85,0:04:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how old was David\Nwhen he became king?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.52,0:04:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says that he “was 30 years old.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.86,0:04:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that when David was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Saul had already been ruling\NIsrael for ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.30,0:04:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But when Saul became king,\NJonathan was a grown man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.17,0:04:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He was probably already in the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to be\Nat least 20 years old to be in the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.14,0:04:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Jonathan was at least 20
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when Saul began to rule\Nand David was born 10 years after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.52,0:05:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what difference in age would there have been
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,between Jonathan and David?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.92,0:05:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,About a 30-year difference
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.76,0:05:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—20 plus 10 equals 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the next one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is a bit more complicated;\Nit’s the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.43,0:05:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can do this. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.50,0:05:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Insight on the Scriptures says
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that Moses and Job lived at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.41,0:05:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Bible doesn’t say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.78,0:05:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.55,0:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I hear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.59,0:05:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right; we do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Job’s test must have occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sometime after the death of Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that because in Job chapter 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah told Satan:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is no one like [Job] on the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.24,0:05:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“No one.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.60,0:05:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if Joseph had still been alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.97,0:06:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would have said that there was\Nno one like Joseph and Job on the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.98,0:06:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the test had occurred earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.28,0:06:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would have said\Nthat there was no one like Jacob and Job,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.58,0:06:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaac and Job, Abraham and Job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.19,0:06:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember, there were\Nonly two years between Noah and Abraham,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can conclude that the test of Job
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.10,0:06:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred after the death of Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.57,0:06:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When did Joseph die?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.27,0:06:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The date is solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.67,0:06:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s 1657 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.27,0:06:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we figure that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.81,0:06:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t like math, trust me,\Nyou don’t want to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But Insight{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}and the Bible will give you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,all the information you need\Nto figure it out for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.29,0:06:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s keep it simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.29,0:06:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go with 1657 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.29,0:06:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s 144 years before Israel left Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.30,0:07:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,under the direction of Moses in 1513 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So Job’s test must have occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.07,0:07:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,sometime within that 144-year period.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is a big hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.25,0:07:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,144 years before Israel left Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.25,0:07:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you beginning to put it together?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.39,0:07:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the clincher:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.89,0:07:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Job lived for 140 years
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,after he passed the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.86,0:07:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so he was probably still alive\Nin the land of Uz
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.87,0:07:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when Israel left Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.90,0:07:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Conclusion: Job and Moses
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.27,0:07:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,definitely lived at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.34,0:07:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what have we learned by doing the math?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.58,0:07:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Superficially, we might say:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.75,0:07:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, we’ve learned that Abraham\Nwas born two years after Noah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.75,0:07:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“And we’ve proved that Jonathan  \Nwas at least 30 years older than David
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:07:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Moses and Job\Ndefinitely lived at the same time.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.40,0:08:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Superficially, we got the answers\Nto those questions, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.43,0:08:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fact is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.43,0:08:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that probably none\Nof those questions ever kept you up at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.51,0:08:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a broader picture here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.74,0:08:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What we’d like you to take away
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.31,0:08:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fact that sometimes a number\Nis more than just a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.25,0:08:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It can provide information\Nthat we couldn’t get any other way,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.95,0:08:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we can understand that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.35,0:08:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this discussion will have been\Nwell worth having.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.36,0:08:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you see a number in the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.19,0:08:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t run the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Embrace it; stop and think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be glad you did.
